cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses the development of manual, semi-manual, and automatic image processing data collection systems to collect microscopic pedestrian data. This falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the behavior of pedestrians in different situations and evaluates design policies. This falls under the domain of social networks and information networks. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the interaction of pedestrians and their movement in pedestrian traffic flow. This falls under the domain of human-computer interaction. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the evaluation of design policies and their impact on pedestrian flow. This falls under the domain of computers and society. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the development of a physical-based microscopic pedestrian simulation model. This falls under the domain of computational engineering.
